value:
Multiplex networks representing different types of genetic interactions, for different organisms. Layers represent (i) physical, (ii) association, (iii) co-localization, (iv) direct, and (v) suppressive, (vi) additive or synthetic genetic interaction. Edge direction (i,j) indicates gene i interacting with gene j.[^icon]
[^icon]: Description obtained from the [ICON](https://icon.colorado.edu) project.
['M. De Domenico, M. A. Porter, & A. Arenas. \MuxViz: a tool for multilayer analysis and visualization of networks\". Journal of Complex Networks
